From 'we are led' to global praise, President Cyril Ramaphosa has received much adoration from South Africans and the global community for his handling to halt the spread of the coronavirus in SA. But on Thursday night, as he addressed the nation on a five-stage lockdown plan to take effect from May 1, it was the end of his speech that had the memes rolling in. Ramaphosa urged South Africans leaving their homes to wear masks. To prove his point, he took a moment to put his mask on at the end of his speech. Only, it, er, didn't go as planned. Of course, the ever so quick interweb folks were ready with them memes. And SA was on the floor giggling... For actual info on the five-stage plan, read these important stories.